originalText.text:
DONT PARK HERE! The guy in charge of parking your car is rude and violates your personal space. I follow the rules and regulations of the place, my car gas tank is low, when I dropped it off at 8am, after 9 hours of work I picked up my car 10 minutes before closing time. First thing he said to me was, “did anyone call you?” I was confused, he said did “Leo” called you?” Leo is My boyfriend my jawed dropped because I never provided this guy with my number, name  or my boyfriend’s number or name.
He called my boyfriend 5 times to tell him “can you bring gas bc her tank its low?” I know my car, my car will make it home or their near gas station. He yelled at me and said “you are not allow to park here I spoke to my supervisor and manager you are not allow here no more”.
Then he kicked me out and drove my car over the ramp, mind you the car will not move bc it was low tank
I was shaking the whole time because how the hell he got my boyfriend number.
He is rude and obviously if you are late or your gas tank is low he will harass you and your personal life.
